    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">1,539</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">2,943</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">Low<br>Indeterminacy</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-1dc460d04615ded511c8\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-1dc460d04615ded511c8\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Low Indeterminacy<\\/b>: >20-40 percent indeterminacy (first prospect of release at 60-79.99 percent of judicial maximum).\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Low Indeterminacy<\\/b>: >20-40 percent indeterminacy (first prospect of release at 60-79.99 percent of judicial maximum).\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">Incarcerated felons of a state correctional institution generally become eligible for parole when they have served the minimum term of an indeterminate sentence or one-quarter of the term of a definite sentence. Some inmates may qualify for an accelerated parole program if they meet certain criteria, apply, and are accepted into the program. The accelerated parole program allows for release eligibility up to three months prior to the original parole eligibility date, contingent on completion of a case management plan tailored to criminogenic needs. In addition to meeting the time requirements for parole, inmates are not eligible for release if they are currently in restrictive housing for a disciplinary violation.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-ef17aa74851ea45d082c\" style=\"width:100%;height:454px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-ef17aa74851ea45d082c\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"width\":500,\"height\":350},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People who are Parole Eligible but Still in Prison by Race in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":false},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0